{"lemma":"نَدْرُ","slug":"نَدْرُ","root":"ن.د.ر","root_slug":"ن-د-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-د-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":0},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n39603"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n39603","headword_ar":"نَدَرَ","root":"ndr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nadorN","text_ar":"نَدْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuduwrN","text_ar":"نُدُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb, K,) [which latter is the more common, if not the only right, form,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It fell,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, Msb, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went, or came, out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forth, from another thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from other things,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from amid a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the inside of a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from among things, so as to be apparent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"standing out to view;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it fell, and became apart, fell off, fell out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came, out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forth, from the generality of things,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the general assemblage, main body, bulk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"common mass, to which it pertained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from other things:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) or, [in some cases,] simply,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it fell,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dropped."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nadara mino qawomihi","text_ar":"نَدَرَ مِنْ قَوْمِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and became separated"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from his people."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nadara mino bayotihi","text_ar":"نَدَرَ مِنْ بَيْتِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went forth from his house"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) I heard one say to his wife,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unoduriY","text_ar":"اُنْدُرِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Go thou forth and be separate:"},{"kind":"text","text":"app. meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be thou divorced"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Z, in the A, immediately following what here immediately precedes.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nadara AlEaZomu","text_ar":"نَدَرَ العَظْمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nadara mino mawoDiEihi","text_ar":"نَدَرَ مِنْ مَوْضِعِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The bone became dislocated"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"displaced."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb.) It is said of a man, in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaD~a yada A=xara fanadara vaniy~atahu","text_ar":"عَضَّ يَدَ ا=خَرَ فَنَدَرَ ثَنِيَّتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or, accord. to another relation,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nadarato","text_ar":"نَدَرَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He bit the arm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hand, of another, and his central incisor dropped out"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nadara TaAy^irN Eano $ajarapK","text_ar":"نَدَرَ طَايِرٌ عَنْ شَجَرَةٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bird dropped and alighted from a tree."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nadara naAdirN mina Aljabali","text_ar":"نَدَرَ نَادِرٌ مِنَ الجَبَلِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A prominence projected,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"jutted out, from the mountain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAba","text_ar":"اَصَابَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaTaru AlHa$iy$a fanadara Alr~uTobu","text_ar":"المَطَرُ الحَشِيشَ فَنَدَرَ الرُّطْبُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The rain fell upon the dry herbage and the fresh herbage came forth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nadara Aln~abaAtu","text_ar":"نَدَرَ النَّبَاتُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The plant put forth its leaves"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from its uppermost branches."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nadarati Al$~ajarapu","text_ar":"نَدَرَتِ الشَّجَرَةُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The tree produced its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuwSap","text_ar":"خُوصَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; (M, K;) which is the case when the camels are able to pasture upon them: (M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became green."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sgh, K.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nadara fiY EilomK","text_ar":"نَدَرَ فِى عِلْمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDolK","text_ar":"فَضْلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IKtt,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY faDolihi","text_ar":"فى فَضْلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He outwent others"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became extraordinary"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (IKtt, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in knowledge"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"science,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in excellence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKtt,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his excellence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nadura AlkalaAmu","text_ar":"نَدُرَ الكَلَامُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)  inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nadaraApN","text_ar":"نَدَرَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"language, was extraordinary"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strange,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[with respect to usage or analogy or both]: (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was the contr. of chaste:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mz, 13th"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nwE","text_ar":"نوع"},{"kind":"text","text":":) [but this explanation requires restriction; for what is extraordinary with respect to usage is the contr. of chaste; but many a word that is extraordinary with respect to analogy is more chaste than a cognate word agreeable with analogy: hence the above phrase is also explained as signifying]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"language, was chaste and good."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Msb","K","T","TA","A","IKtt"]}]}}